A feature I like in golang is the hability to declare a variable at the assignation time. Something like this:
foo := &#34;bar&#34; Here the variable foo will automatically set up as a string with the value &ldquo;bar&rdquo;. One more feature is to be able to allocate on same line as doing a comparison. Like this:
if foo := &#34;bar&#34;; foo == &#34;baz&#34; { // do something } else { // do something else } This is really handy when it comes to catch errors from an other function:
